OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1775628243
OL,3,CPilot scheme launches to change
OL,4,Cbehaviour of high-risk domestic abusers
OL,6,F"We must work together to challenge
OL,7,Fand change dangerous behaviours,
OL,8,Frobustly monitor and manage those who
OL,9,Fpose a risk, and give victims and
OL,10,Ftheir children the support they need."
OL,12,FDuring the project, independent
OL,13,Fdomestic violence advisors will
OL,14,Fsupport the victim at the same time.
OL,16,FResults from pilots in other parts of
OL,17,Fthe UK have seen percentages of
OL,18,Fperpetrators using physical abuse cut
OL,19,Fby 82%, sexual abuse by 88%, stalking
OL,20,Fbehaviours by 75% and jealous and
OL,21,Fcontrolling behaviours by 73%.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@fO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
